Class PageRect

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.band.tiles.pages.PageRect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public final class PageRect
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    Class that represents the x and y location of the upper left corner of a Microsoft Band layout element, relative to its parent element, as well as its width and height

        public PageRect(int originX,
        int originY,
        int width,
        int height)
        Constructor that creates a new PageRect with the given values
        Parameters:
        originX - The value to set as the X origin of this Rectangle (Should be set to 0 if the parent element will be a FlowPanel or a ScrollFlowPanel)
        originY - The value to set as the Y origin of this Rectangle (Should be set to 0 if the parent element will be a FlowPanel or a ScrollFlowPanel)
        width - The value to set as the width of this Rectangle
        height - The value to set as the height of this Rectangle
